# Implementation Plan - Phase 41: Improvement of Song Slide Presentation

This plan outlines the enhancements to the song slide lyrics presentation, introducing a toggleable "Line Break" option in presentation settings, saving it to the database, and dynamically processing lyrics to split long lines at commas to improve display aesthetics on various screen aspect ratios.

---

## 1. Objectives & UI Requirements

### 1.1 Line Break Logic Requirements
- **Goal**: When song lyrics lines are too long, avoid excessively shrinking the font size. Instead, wrap long lines elegantly.
- **Specific comma-based splitting**:
  - If a line is too long and contains commas (`,`), it should split at a comma. If multiple commas are present, split at the comma that yields the most balanced lengths (i.e., closest to the center character-wise).
  - If a line is too long and does not contain commas, let it wrap naturally (at spaces / word boundaries) instead of forcing a comma-based split.
  - If a line is short, do not break it.
- **Constraint**: Only apply this new line break logic when the user enables the "Line Break" option in the presentation settings. Otherwise, maintain the current layout behavior (each line is forced on a single line by shrinking font size, unless too long to shrink further).

### 1.2 Settings & Database Persistence
- Add a new boolean field `lyricsLineBreak` (default `false`) to `PresentationSettings`.
- Expose this option in the typography settings dialog for lyrics in the Song settings tab of the Presentation Settings dialog.
- Persist the option in the Isar database and sync configuration.

